=item * B<Whitelist of approved plugins> - Only plugins listed in the manifest
can be loaded.

=item * B<Whitelist of allowed actions> - Only pre-approved subroutine names
can be invoked on plugins.

=item * B<File permission checks> - Plugin files and the manifest must be owned
by root and must not be world-writable.

=item * B<Path traversal prevention> - Plugin filenames are validated to prevent
directory traversal attacks.

=item * B<Execution timeout> - Plugin actions are subject to a timeout to prevent
denial of service.

=item * B<Input validation> - Plugin names and action names are validated against
strict patterns.

